  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal framework surrounding money laundering:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) standards\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- International money laundering prevention protocols\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Patriot Act\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n\n3. Reporting Requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Currency Transaction Reports\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Customer due diligence obligations\n\n4. Legal Consequences\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Financial institution monitoring\n- Transaction tracking\n- Risk assessment frameworks\n- Internal control systems\n\n6. Jurisdictional Approaches\n- Varying legal standards across countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n7. Emerging Technologies\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Enhanced technological surveillance\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes globally.",
